# Loops in Java

## for Loop

Used when you know exact number of iterations.

```java
for (initialization; condition; update) {
    // code
}
```

**Example**: Print 1 to 5
```java
for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    System.out.println(i);
}
```

## while Loop

Repeat while condition is true.

```java
while (condition) {
    // code
    // update condition
}
```

**Example**: Count down from 5
```java
int i = 5;
while (i > 0) {
    System.out.println(i);
    i--;
}
```

## do-while Loop

Execute once, then check condition.

```java
do {
    // code (always executes at least once)
} while (condition);
```

## Loop Control Statements

â€¢ **break**: Exit loop immediately

â€¢ **continue**: Skip current iteration

â€¢ **return**: Exit method

**Example**:
```java
for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
    if (i == 5) {
        break;  // exits when i = 5
    }
    System.out.println(i);
}
```

