# 1D Arrays in Java

An array stores multiple values of same type in contiguous memory.

## Array Declaration

```java
int[] numbers;              // Declaration
int[] numbers = new int[5]; // Declaration + Allocation
```

## Array Initialization

```java
// Method 1: With values
int[] scores = {90, 85, 95, 88, 92};

// Method 2: New keyword
int[] scores = new int[5];
scores[0] = 90;
scores[1] = 85;
```

## Array Indexing

Arrays are 0-indexed:
```java
int[] arr = {10, 20, 30};
arr[0] = 10;   // First element
arr[1] = 20;   // Second element
arr[2] = 30;   // Third element
```

## Array Length

```java
int[] arr = {10, 20, 30};
int length = arr.length;  // 3
```

## Iterating Through Array

```java
int[] scores = {90, 85, 95};

// for loop
for (int i = 0; i < scores.length; i++) {
    System.out.println(scores[i]);
}

// for-each loop
for (int score : scores) {
    System.out.println(score);
}
```

