# Classes & Objects in Java

OOP organizes code into classes and objects.

## Class Structure

```java
public class Car {
    // Attributes (Data)
    private String color;
    private String brand;
    private int speed;

    // Methods (Behavior)
    public void accelerate() {
        speed += 10;
    }

    public void brake() {
        speed -= 10;
    }
}
```

## Creating Objects

```java
Car myCar = new Car();  // Create object
myCar.accelerate();     // Call method
```

## Access Modifiers

â€¢ **public**: Accessible everywhere

â€¢ **private**: Only within class

â€¢ **protected**: Within package and subclasses

â€¢ **default**: Within package only

## Constructors

Special method called when object is created.

```java
public class Car {
    private String brand;

    // Constructor
    public Car(String brand) {
        this.brand = brand;
    }
}

// Create object
Car myCar = new Car("Toyota");
```

