# Inheritance in Java

Inheritance allows class to acquire properties of another class.

## Parent & Child Classes

```java
// Parent (Super) Class
public class Animal {
    public void eat() {
        System.out.println("Animal is eating");
    }
}

// Child (Sub) Class
public class Dog extends Animal {
    public void bark() {
        System.out.println("Dog is barking");
    }
}
```

## Using Inheritance

```java
Dog dog = new Dog();
dog.eat();   // Inherited from Animal
dog.bark();  // Own method
```

## Method Overriding

Child class provides new implementation.

```java
public class Dog extends Animal {
    @Override
    public void eat() {
        System.out.println("Dog is eating dog food");
    }
}
```

## Types of Inheritance

â€¢ **Single**: Child extends one parent

â€¢ **Multilevel**: A extends B, B extends C

â€¢ **Hierarchical**: Multiple children from one parent

