# Collections: Map Interface

Maps store key-value pairs.

## HashMap

Fast, unordered access.

```java
import java.util.HashMap;

HashMap<String, Integer> ages = new HashMap<>();
ages.put("Alice", 25);  // Add
ages.put("Bob", 30);
ages.put("Charlie", 28);

System.out.println(ages.get("Bob"));  // Get value: 30
ages.remove("Alice");  // Remove
```

## TreeMap

Sorted by key, slower but ordered.

```java
import java.util.TreeMap;

TreeMap<String, Integer> scores = new TreeMap<>();
scores.put("Math", 95);
scores.put("Science", 88);
scores.put("English", 92);
// Automatically sorted by key
```

## Iterating Maps

```java
HashMap<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
map.put("A", 1);
map.put("B", 2);

// Using entrySet
for (Map.Entry<String, Integer> entry : map.entrySet()) {
    System.out.println(entry.getKey() + ": " + entry.getValue());
}
```

